The investigation is being conducted by the Central Operational Unit of the Gendarmerie, a group charged with crimes committed at the municipal level, whose members, in addition to arrests, have conducted eleven searches, primarily at companies associated with the detainees, which operate in Madrid, Vigo, Murcia, Pontevedra, Las Rozas (Madrid) and Totana.
Only one person was arrested in Totana: the owner of a well-known poultry product company in the area, who could have played a mediating role in the case.
The Nuaria Group would have created the largest residential complex in Totana, with 5,000 apartments, a golf course and two wellness hotels.
