What kind of insurance is right for me?
Motor insurance, which provides security for the car owner in the face of various damage events, entails a significant expense and depends on several factors, such as age, gender, date of obtaining a driving license, marital status, type of car to be insured and the type and type of use of the car.
Buying a car is only the first step.
In fact, choosing the right insurance is often more difficult than deciding what kind of car you want.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured.
This agreement takes the form of an insurance contract, which states that the insurance company undertakes to pay compensation in exchange for a fixed insurance premium in the event of an accident.
The insurance premium is basically the amount paid for the insurance, which is determined taking into account various factors, such as age, gender, date of obtaining a driving license, marital status, type of car to be insured, its use, and more.
Insurance companies determine the premium based on statistics, i.e. a higher amount is paid by the person who represents a higher risk of accident.
That’s why women over the age of 25, or women, pay less because statistics show them to be at lower risk because they’re more cautious.
Similarly, on the basis of reports, insurance companies have concluded that married people also cause fewer accidents than lonely people.
The frequency of the use of the car is crucial.
With more frequent use, the possibility of an accident increases.
Many factors are taken into account by insurance companies when setting the premium.
Therefore, the owner should carefully look into it so that he can choose the most appropriate form of insurance for his profile.
In the following, the most important factors for selection are presented in order to best adapt to the needs of the insured and to establish an acceptable price.
When concluding an insurance contract, people under the age of 25 face a number of disadvantages, such as a lack of driving experience and the freshness of their driver’s license.
Although it is ideal to be protected against all dangers, there are also more economical solutions.
More cautious drivers will be able to take out full insurance on their own, thus insuring against all dangers, and the price will also be affordable.
In this type of contract, the insured pays part of the damage.
"The amount of the excess that the insured pays depends on the insurance premium; the higher the premium, the lower the excess," says Luis Noguera, head of First Europa in Spain, the online insurance broker.
Another option is extended third party liability insurance, where the customer insures himself against damage to others, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, you will be insured against theft, fire damage and the loss of the car.
A word of advice.
If you are under the age of 25, be careful and avoid accidents as much as possible, as this will affect the bonus and thus reduce the amount you will have to pay in the future.
A bonus is a discount compared to the basic rate of the insurance company.
The penalty charged in relation to the basic rate is called a malus.
"The amount of bonus and malus depends on the insurance company and its profits.
If the company has had a good year, you can afford to raise the bonus rate,” explains Noguera.
Once the 25-year age limit has been exceeded, it is easier for owners to take out adequate insurance, as the risk of accidents is reduced thanks to the experience gained over the years.
We advise you to take out full insurance.
"In general, young people are not yet able to properly apply their experience during an accident, or even when driving," says the director of the European insurance company in Spain, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of driving, when the drivers have already overcome the fear of beginners.
If the insured person is already married but does not have children yet, it is best to take out full insurance, provided that your financial possibilities allow it.
Insurance companies consider married couples with children to be the clients with the lowest risk, so the fee to be paid in their case is also lower.
In this case, it is best to have complete insurance with a self-portrait (this can reach 300 euros), or if they have a higher bonus, from the third year of the car, they can extend the insurance to damage caused to others.
“They drive more relaxed, but also have more purchasing power and can afford to have a higher deductible,” Luis Noguera said.
For pensioners, we recommend full insurance with self-payment (which is around 150 euros), or in the case of a higher bonus, it can be extended to liability insurance.
Car insurance is a very important thing, not only because it provides protection for the owner in the event of an accident, but also because it is a big expense, so it is essential to choose the right form of personal insurance.
