Following a 2006 Al-Qaeda-sponsored attack on the world’s largest oil processing facility in Abqaiq, Saudi Arabia began building a 35,000-strong rapid reaction force to protect the facilities.
According to the report, 18 of those arrested belong to a cell led by a “specialist in rocket launches” who crosses the border illegally.
The report also said that the fighters had tried to smuggle eight shells into the kingdom.
