These aren't Warhol's crates.
Anyone who associates the concepts of Sweden and the wooden box with each other is thinking of Ikea, not Andy Warhol.
Or is it?
Currently, wooden chests made in Sweden cast a dark shadow on the list of Warhol's works.
Most of the ninety-four "Stockholm-type" Brillo Boxes listed here are forgeries.
After the Swedish newspaper "Expressen" doubted the authenticity of Andy Warhol's 1968 Brillo Boxes a few months ago, now the internal investigation of Moderna Museet in Stockholm has come to a sobering conclusion: The six "Brillo Box" copies donated to Moderna Museet by Pontus Hultén, a former museum director, in 1995 - and most likely one hundred more "Brillo Boxes" on the international art market
The prehistory is a long and complicated, confusing chain of artistic and curatorial feats.
Warhol created his first "Brillo Boxes" in New York in 1964 - painted wooden boxes based on the red-blue-white design of the cardboard box of "Brillo" soap powder.
At an exhibition of his works at the Moderna Museet in 1968, with the approval of Warhol, hundreds of cardboard Brillo boxes were exhibited: These (for cost-saving reasons) did not come from Warhol, but were delivered directly from the Brillo cardboard factory.
It was not about works of art, but about their templates and simple pieces of exhibition.
At the same time, in 1968, Warhol gave permission to produce some of the Brillo wooden crates in Sweden, which, however, were not exhibited in the Moderna Museet.
The witnesses of the time now speak of about fifteen chests which, at that time certified as the Original-Andy-Warhol-Brillo-Box, were rightly included in the history of art and auction under the designation "Stockholm type".
Some were auctioned for more than $100,000.
The problem, however, is that the legendary museum director Pontus Hultén later falsely claimed that about a hundred wooden crates were manufactured and exhibited in Sweden in 1968, which Warhol left to him.
In fact, Hultén’s 105 chests were only manufactured in 1990 for an exhibition in St. Petersburg.
By that time, however, Warhol had been dead for three years.
Lars Bystr<0xC3><0xB6>m, the main monumental caretaker of Moderna Museet, examined six Brillo Boxes, owned by the museum, as well as three Swedish privately owned boxes, two of which were made in Stockholm in 1968: The pressed chipboards were first flattened and polished, then the white oil paint was applied with a brush.
The structure of the 1990 copies, on the other hand, shows that the paint was applied directly to the chipboard with a paint roller, without a foundation - and this is not an oil paint, but an acrylic paint.
“These crates are not certified by the artist and should therefore be removed from the official list of Andy Warhol Brillo Boxes,” says Lars Nittve, director of Moderna Museet: “Unless the Andy Warhol Art Authentication Board in New York decides otherwise, Moderna Museet will classify the six crates in its collection as copies/exhibition material.”
The Authentication Board announced in June that it was investigating "serious allegations" of soap dust crates.
Since then, however, they have been indulging in inexorable silence.
Rebel forces in Manila surrender
Soldiers in the Philippines who barricaded themselves in a hotel in Manila and demanded the overthrow of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo.
He cannot be held responsible for the carnage, said Antonio Trillanes, who accused the president of corruption and election fraud.
Prior to this, the hotel was stormed by government soldiers using tear gas.
The two dozen soldiers had barricaded themselves in the building for hours.
Half of the team were on trial on Thursday for the 2003 failed coup attempt, including Trillanes.
He used the trial to get rid of 30 sympathizers all of a sudden.
The military police charged with guarding the man apparently switched to him and joined the mutiny.
They entered the Peninsula Hotel and demanded the overthrow of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo.
Government units have sealed off the area around the prestigious hotel.
The president has called an emergency meeting of the security cabinet.
Security adviser Norberto Gonzales condemned the soldiers' actions.
"People have had enough," said Trillanes.
"We invite people to join us."
General Danilo Lim, who had previously commanded the Scout Rangers, stated that other units of the army wanted to join the march in a short time.
Critics of the government on Friday called for a strong protest against the president.
The government has been facing corruption allegations for several months.
As early as 2003, the financial district of Manila was the main scene of an attempted mutiny against Arroyo by about 200 members of the military.
The uprising failed after less than 24 hours when the army refused to join.
Since 1986, there have been at least seven attempted coups in the Philippines against democratically elected governments.
United Internet becomes a major shareholder in Versatel
United Internet has acquired more than 20 percent of Versatel.
As the company announced on Wednesday evening, the average price per share is 14.46 euros.
This represents a 20.05 percent stake in the share capital.
There have been speculations about the takeover before.
The possibility of increasing the share acquired in Versatel remains open.
The move is aimed at consolidating the German DSL market, according to United Internet.
Earlier on Wednesday, assumptions were made about a possible merger, after Berenberg Bank increased its stake in the D<0xC3><0xBC>sseldorf network operator by a further 5 percent to 15.1 percent.
The financial institution reserves the share only to a third party, it is reported on the financial market.
On the previous day, United Internet already owned just under 10 percent of the mobile phone company Drillisch.
As part of the capital increase, Drillisch issued 17.4 million new shares worth 106.4 million euros.
United Internet bought 5.15 million shares for 31.4 million euros.
In addition, the companies initiated a dialogue on cooperation on the launch of DSL and mobile phone products.
"We are strengthening our partnership," a spokesman for the United Internet said.
The two companies jointly established the MSP joint venture to take over the competing Freenet.
The two companies are initially content with a good 10 percent stake in Freenet and will not exercise their right to take over another 18.49 percent of Freenet, United Internet said on Thursday.
However, the two companies are leaving all options open, in particular to increase their shareholding in Freenet AG.
Negotiations between United Internet and Freenet on the strategic partnership were concluded in mid-November.
The poker game around Freenet, which has been going on for months now and which can only be seen with ease, is part of the consolidation of the German telecommunications market.
At the end of the third quarter, Freenet had 2.9 million contracted mobile phone customers and 1.27 million DSL and fixed line access customers.
The holding company formed by United Internet and Drillisch has so far held a direct 6.01% stake in Freenet.
Now it has been agreed that Drillisch will bring in an additional round four percent.
The acquisition of 18.49 percent of the investment company Vatas was agreed in August.
